==Chinese==

===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|尗|又|ls=ic|ls2=psc|t1=wooden stake|t2=hand|c1=p|c2=s}} – using a wooden stake to dig the ground. Later phonetically borrowed to mean "paternal uncle".

The whole character is partly related to [[建]] since it represents a hand planting a wooden stake in the ground.

===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|alt=尗,𠁮,𡬟,𡬧,𡭫,𭣬,𠦑,𢆑}} {{attn|zh|are all these forms used for this etymology?}}
{{zh-ref|Sagart (1999)}} connects it to {{och-l|督|tr=*ᵃtuk|middle}} and reconstructs the {{cog|och|-}} as ''*ᵇs-tuk'', the prefix possibly having a nominalizing function.

Alternatively, {{zh-ref|Starostin}} proposes a possible derivation from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*m-(t/d)u|*t(h)u (~ -iw)|nephew}} and reconstructs the {{cog|och|-}} as ''*tikʷ'' (< ''*tiw-k''?) ~ ''*tu-k''.

